The paper deals with boosting, a popular machine learning approach, and proposes the first agnostic online boosting algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves online learning and convex optimization, which are relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category, as it proposes an efficient reduction to online convex optimization.
